<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="576" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[791,1384,1107,1531]" lastBlockId="92.[177,1385,1537,3464]" pageId="92" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicName box="[792,1050,1261,1294]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">Artibeus planirostris</taxonomicName>
1s in subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1377,1261,1294]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Artibeus</taxonomicName>
. Along with other similar taxa, such as A. 
<taxonomicName box="[833,950,1348,1373]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schwartzi">schwartzi</taxonomicName>
, and A. 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1233,1348,1373]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aequatorialis">aequatorialis</taxonomicName>
, it was formerly identified as a subspecies of the very variable A. 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1094,1427,1452]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jamaicensis">jamaicensis</taxonomicName>
, but it is now considered a full species based on phylogenetic analysis of DNA sequences and morphological studies. Several names have been linked to A. 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1065,1537,1570]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">planirostris</taxonomicName>
; trinitatis and grenadensiswere considered the same entity and listed under A. 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1095,1577,1610]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jamaicensis">jamaicensis</taxonomicName>
, but they are related to A. 
<taxonomicName box="[250,394,1616,1649]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="576" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">planirostris</taxonomicName>
based on molecular and dental characters. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
